  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>What Haier washer repair costs in LA</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Waived with repair</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Inlet valve</td><td>$80 – $140</td><td>Won't-fill diagnostic</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Drain pump</td><td>$160 – $240</td><td>Clear debris filter first</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Door latch / lock mechanism</td><td>$120 – $200</td><td>HLC front-load</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Motor assembly</td><td>$280 – $440</td><td>GE Appliances cross-fit likely</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Main control board</td><td>$240 – $380</td><td>Haier-SKU specific</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Bellows / door boot seal (HLC)</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>Front-load seal wear</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Shock absorbers (HLC, pair)</td><td>$140 – $220</td><td>Vibration / walking</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Portable-washer casters (HLP)</td><td>$60 – $120</td><td>Portable-specific</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Faucet quick-connect hose (HLP)</td><td>$40 – $80</td><td>HLP fill connector</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="small">Related: <a href="/brands/haier/">Haier brand hub</a> · <a href="/brands/ge-washer-repair/">GE washer (GE Appliances parent-chain peer)</a> · <a href="/brands/ge-repair/">GE Appliances brand hub</a> · <a href="/services/washer-repair/">Washer repair (service hub)</a> · <a href="/price-list/washer-repair-cost/">Washer repair cost</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>The compact-washer niche in LA — where Haier fits</h2>
    <p>LA has an unusually high density of apartments + ADUs + compact-condo installs where a full-size 4.3-5.0 cu ft US washer won't fit or isn't practical. That's Haier's niche in the US residential market. The HLC compact front-load (1.5-2.4 cu ft, 24-inch width) installs under counters or stacks in small closets where conventional 27-inch washers can't. The HLP portable roll-away connects to a kitchen faucet with a quick-adapter hose and drains into the sink — perfect for apartments without dedicated laundry hookup, or for ADUs where permanent plumbing isn't practical. The HLPW high-capacity compact (2.6-3.2 cu ft) bridges the gap for slightly-larger laundry closets that can't quite accommodate a full-size install.</p>
    <p>Capacity tradeoff is the honest conversation: you'll run more cycles per week vs a full-size washer for the same laundry volume, and larger items (king bedding, heavy comforters) often don't fit. For the right install constraints, Haier compact is the correct answer — and Haier's 2016 acquisition of GE Appliances means parts-chain longevity that earlier Chinese-brand entrants didn't offer.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
